th the release of DAOC). They can put more and more awesome melee loot in the game, increasing the power of the class exponentially.<br>
<br>
But for wizards, there always seems to be a hidden cost.<br>
<br>
Let's give them Harvest, but make it stun then for a long period of time, and make sure to implement it with a statement by Abashi that &quot;Wizards will be receiving some changes soon, but not because of any perceived lack in the class design.&quot;<br>
<br>
Let's give them anti-gate (translocational suppression) spells, but it will silence them for 30seconds after casting.<br>
<br>
Let's give them a familiar, but make it cost them 1250hp/mana if it dies or poofs.<br>
<br>
Let's give them Rain spells, but leave the 3rd wave broken for 3 years, thus eliminating any possible mana efficiency of the spell, and therefore group attractiveness as well. While we're at it, lets make the PULL AND MEZ THE ADDS method of grouping the only viable method by adding insane MR to mobs in any zone where a wizard can really kick some ass, thereby elimitaing rains in grouping for fear of breaking the mez.<br>
<br>
Let's give them awesome AE spells that are only useful in a group because of the need for chain-stun by an enchanter. But, if they every find a good zone to use it in, lets eliminate its use by totally destroying that zone.<br>
<br>
Let's give them a massive nuke series called BANE, but make it useful against only a handful of monsters in the game, difficult to get, and make it cost 20pp per cast.<br>
<br>
Let's give them increased mana regen in the form of a familiar/buff, but make it take back 1250mana later to make them pay for that increased regen.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I am so sick of Veran't way of dealing with the wizard class.<br>
<br>
<br>
p.s.<br>
<br>
